triparted.d:
a. Parted into three piece; having three parts or pieces;
   -- said of the field or of a bearing; as, a cross triparted.
a. Divided nearly to the base into three segments or lobes.

tripolitan.d:
a. Of or pertaining to Tripoli or its inhabitants;
   Tripoline.
n. A native or inhabitant of Tripoli.

trisnitrate.d:
n. A nitrate formed from three molecules of nitric acid;
   also, less properly, applied to certain basic nitrates; as, trisnitrate
   of bismuth.

triturate.d:
v. t. To rub, grind, bruise, or thrash.
v. t. To rub or grind to a very fine or impalpable powder;
   to pulverize and comminute thoroughly.

triumphing.d:
p. pr. & vb. n. of Triumph
a. Having or celebrating a triumph; victorious;
   triumphant.

tryptics.d:
plural of tryptic
a. Relating to trypsin or to its action; produced by trypsin;
   as, trypsin digestion.
